data.title: Lunch
data.text: Lunch was good. Had the special (chicken pot pie). Dessert was pretty good. Cheesecakes seem to be the popular choice here with a good variety to try. They make portions that share for two.   We had the Turtle Cheesecake. Carmel and chocolate on top of a rich cheesecake. Pretty good. Enjoy.

data.title: Good food, good location in downtown, try the sweets
data.text: We ate here today and three of us had the chicken salad stuffed tomatoes and strawberry pretzel salads and others had luncheon sandwiches and chips.  I like the chicken salad because it does not have fruit and nuts in it.  The strawberry pretzel salad was good.   The cookies are DELICIOUS, moist and chewy.  My husband said, "thumbs up" on the Dulce de Leche cheesecake.  The prices are reasonable and the service was good.
